message: Hello future player! The 'growth serum' (ğŸŒ¡ï¸) is great for initial value boosts, use it until items plateau. message: Focus heavily on the Growth Serum! Apply it to base ingredients to make them 'grown' (value 5-15). Apply serum a second time to 'grown' *hybrids* to make them 'super-grown' (value 20-30). Sometimes, a third serum on a 'super-grown' hybrid can reach 'ultra-grown' with even higher value (e.g., 30-45). However, applying serum too many times, especially to single ingredients or 'ultra-grown' items, almost always makes the value negative. The Mutation Catalyst consistently reduces item value; avoid it entirely. Combine similar base animals (e.g., two small air animals or two medium water animals) early on to create initial hybrids. Combining 'grown' or 'super-grown' animals/hybrids can also increase value, but too many components in a hybrid seem to drastically reduce its value.

message: Focus on the 'growth serum'. It's very beneficial for small and medium items, increasing their value in stages (grown, super-grown, ultra-grown) up to 15. For large items, use 'growth serum' only once to get them to 'grown' status (value 15); applying it a second time to large items will make their value negative. The 'mutation catalyst' always leads to negative values, so avoid it. Combine two 'grown' items of the same size, especially large ones from different environments (e.g., grown land-large + grown water-large) for the highest scores (up to 35). Combining small 'grown' items also yields good value (15).
